ow_down` backoff, `maxPollInterval` cap, `maxExpiresIn` cap, empty-token edge case, and unknown error codes all have zero test coverage.\\n\\n**Important (7 items):**\\n- `NewClient` is not injectable into `runLogin`, making unit testing difficult (item 3)\\n- `os.CreateTemp` + `Chmod` has a brief window with wider permissions; `os.OpenFile` with explicit mode would be safer for token files (item 4)\\n- Happy-path integration test does not verify approval URL structure (item 5)\\n- Token file path printed to stdout on success (item 6)\\n- `SaveToken` does not validate empty token input (item 7)\\n- `\\\"entire-cli\\\"` client ID hardcoded in two places without a constant (item 8)\\n- `ResolveURLFromBase` does not validate the base URL scheme (item 9)\\n\\n**Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES** -- primarily due to the unaddressed review-01 items and the new transient-error-handling and test-coverage gaps.\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a713062a872c2d8d3 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 64658\\ntool_uses: 36\\nduration_ms: 595619</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"88d3ad3e-bcda-4dea-a853-ed554a1ed549\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-14T10:05:00.451Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"Review the changes in the `feat/device-auth-login` branch compared to `main`. The diff adds ~1156 lines across 11 files implementing an OAuth device authorization flow for the `entire login` CLI command.\\n\\nHere's a summary of what was added:\\n\\n## New files:\\n1. **`cmd/entire/cli/api/base_url.go`** + test — Resolves the Entire API base URL (defaults to `https://entire.io`, overridden by `ENTIRE_API_BASE_URL` env var)\\n2. **`cmd/entire/cli/auth/client.go`** + test — HTTP client for device auth (POST `/oauth/device/code` to start, POST `/oauth/token` to poll)\\n3. **`cmd/entire/cli/auth/store.go`** + test — Token persistence to `~/.config/entire/auth.json` keyed by base URL, with atomic writes (temp file + rename) and 0600 permiss